This paper is about conversational datasets and evaluation metrics for conversational response selection models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also discusses machine learning models, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper presents several baselines and a neural encoder model, which are related to machine learning and deep learning, respectively, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible sub-category. The paper also involves information retrieval techniques for data filtering, so cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper does not explicitly mention any specific sub-category, but it could be related to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) if the focus is on the efficiency and scalability of the models and datasets.
